 <p><a name="stpa_o320"><a name="70326-0016.htm_para22"><a name="07032631000243">Frequently, what is said about children and child poverty is a way of thinking about how to construct a new and better society. Looking at things from a child&#146;s point of view offers a vantage point from which to offer critiques of society as a whole. It is the child&#146;s position as a future adult that is of interest to politicians. That has always been true&#151;it was true in ancient Sparta, it was true under the Jesuits and it was true for Bismarck. That is largely because we know, or we think we know, that what happens to us as children is a significant influence on our lives when we become adults. It is extremely tempting to believe that by controlling the condition of childhood we can reach into the future and control the society that we want.</p>
 
